Today we will learn one game of d11,
it was played in the last WC.
As you see, the last big tournament is still "hot" so we have many games about it.
D11 is hot in WC by Email 2003
The game of d11, which was not noticed by most people during the tournament,
but it specially caught my attention.
The game was played between two Swedes,
This is the main theory of d11 nowadays.
Move 11-i11 has become more popular recently,
and so it was also played in this WC.
It was hard for me to predict who would win in the game - Andersson or Karlsson,
but usually, white gets the better position here,
and the white's win chances are better.
Who thinks black wins here more than whites?
sometimes, your opinion may be different from mine
always hard to tell for me
he played a lot 11-i11 in email games
I once had a game where I was white,
and I won here by this 14
do you see white has VCF
so this black move would block it.
who would want to show win here?
4x3x3 is still forbidden as you know
That is why this 13 is played very often instead.
Now, there are many different 14th moves,
When I played with Carlsson, I used j9
and Stefan Karlsson used same variant against Tord
These 17 moves are kind of theory here
and the result is white advantage in peaceful style
has anyone of you played this 18th move before?
This variant has been very big mystery
most people do not really know what is happening here
white is active, black is active
both attack and defend same time
and what is the final outcome..
well, that is what we will see now
somebody make a mistake and opponents win
well, in this variant, the problem lies much deeper
if you will see the game, and i ask you , where was mistake
maybe none of you is able to tell just now
are you implying the mistake has happened ?
okay secret  .. we will see later :p
in this game, its is very very hard to tell,
black has to be active, to keep tempo
indeed, k10 blocks the k11 threat
the interesting part of this variant is,
black seems to be able to block the cut from both ends
which would make the L8 real 4x3 again
but there is a question of timing.. while black blocks to g6, white will have enough time to take j10
so there is no 4x3 at L8
from this moment, L8 is real danger
but white has the speed now
I have played many games of this variant,
especially in the summer camp, for training.
And many others have tried it too,
but nobody really focused on the real situation here.
The first person who was really interested in the real problem here was russian player Salnikov
he talked to me on ICQ (about a year ago maybe),
and we discussed the dangers of this variant.
It is clear that the safe style is in favor of whites
